pois.note: Fill up with water. Powerline climb with some hab there. Long stretch of dirt road.
pois.name: Boulton Creek

pois.note: Stores on the right before crossing river to the left. Minigas is right on route. Fill up on everything. Lot of road to Sparwood.
pois.name: Elkford

pois.note: Arriving via Elk Hwy. Right on Aspen Drive goes to stores. Last service until border. Rivers everywhere. Pave road to Corban with no life. Get ready for the scary part. Watch for deep crossing.
pois.name: Sparwood

places.note: On the right after crossing Hwy
places.name: 7 Eleven

pois.note: It is not the first cabin. Cabin is on the right hand side.
pois.name: Butts Cabin

places.note: Not a good idea unless very hungry. Gas station down the road instead.
places.name: First and Last chance bar

pois.note: Abundant stream water afterwards. Go over flathhead pass. Watch out for sharp rocks down to dirt road. No services until Whitefish. May be snow on red meadow pass.
pois.name: Eureka

pois.note: Most services seem to be across the rail road. Safeway is 1 mile off road. Gas station and restaurants are closer. Readlly flat for a while.
pois.name: Whitefish

pois.note: Services on Nucleus st (on route).
pois.name: Columbia Falls

pois.note: In case of emergency, contact Kathleen at Laughing Horse Lodge 406-886-2080.
pois.name: Swan River

pois.note: Gas station/ market off route when going straight on Hwy 209. Gets pretty remote quickly to holland lake. Make noise in single track.
pois.name: Ferndale

pois.note: slightly off route on 83 at Jetty. Don't go unless desperate.
pois.name: Hungry Bear

pois.note: bottom of richmond peak. Food but don't depend on it if possible.
pois.name: Holland Lake

pois.note: offroute. Just go to Ovando.
pois.name: Seeley Lake

pois.note: From Helena, lot of uphill. Get on the Lava Trail. Lots of walking.
pois.name: Basin

pois.note: Have them go through my bike and safeway is across the street.
pois.name: Butte

pois.note: From Butte. Trail goes to bottom of flicer ridge between two patches of forest. Single track trail. DO NOT RIDE.
pois.name: Wise River

places.note: Pump for water if at night. Use tab.
places.name: Firehouse

pois.note: Next is Bannack, can be muddy
pois.name: Polaris

pois.note: From pave road to lima, no service. Nothing. Go fast if rain is coming. Can be super muddy. If getting to road and really bad shape, make left along highway, 0.5 mile there is a store at Cabins.
pois.name: Lima

pois.note: Hard riding from Lima. RV park with candy before as well.
pois.name: Sawtelle Mountain Resort

pois.note: Pack for flag ranch
pois.name: Warm River

pois.note: There is water outside
pois.name: Squirrel Creek Elk Ranch

pois.note: Store with batteries. Tons of food.
pois.name: Flagg Ranch Resort

pois.note: Alternate on a super steep hab north of pinedale.
pois.name: Pinedale

pois.note: Last chance to get food for the Basin.
pois.name: Boulder

pois.note: Before, on the highway there is a rest area, I can fill up for Basin. Clean myself up.
pois.name: South Pass City

pois.note: Don't rely on it. Can sleep in Tipi in from of the bar.
pois.name: Atlantic City

pois.note: there is also a reservoir off route.
pois.name: Diagnus Well

pois.note: From basin, on a paved road and turn left to Lodge. Right before, Post office, may be able to ask for water. Climb.
pois.name: Brush Mountain Lodge

pois.note: Careful on descent after lodge
pois.name: Clark

pois.note: No water
pois.name: Radium

pois.note: 1.5 miles off route, continue on 9 instead of right on 33.
pois.name: Kremmling

pois.note: Ghost town.
pois.name: Summitville

pois.note: infamous dogs. Check location of Snack shack somewhere on the road to Vallecitos?
pois.name: Vallecitos

pois.note: Tarmac all the way to Grants. Cross Indian reservation.
pois.name: Cuba

pois.note: 24/7 gas station are in town not later. Pack for the end. Now give 100%. All flat from there, more weight is ok.
pois.name: Silver City

pois.note: Do not rely on this place.
pois.name: Hachita
